Mix one part [[mineral spirits]] into two parts boiled [[linseed oil]].  A little [[Lamp black]] or [[Iron oxide]] can be added for a black or brown color.  Coat both sides of a good quality cotton canvas with the mixture.  Let dry for one week.

The resulting cloth is flexible, water resistant, and perfect for outdoor use.

